{
  "stem": "107.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't have any luggage.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had again a bucket in the corner.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But we could keep the doors-- you know, the-- the cattle door-- open so that we had some air.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this long trip through all Germany, from Poland through Germany to-- to Berlin.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Next station was Berlin.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There we came to Sachsenhausen or Oranienburg-- I think Sachsenhausen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Sachsenhausen was one of the oldest and biggest concentration camps in-- outside of Berlin, in the middle of Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there we were for a month in quarantine.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now this time it was a real quarantine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They wanted to be sure when we get out, and to work, that we don't carry lice, or fleas, or illnesses, and can work.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We got the showers, and disinfections, and got shots, and all kinds of things, not nearly enough food, but enough so that we survived-- one piece of bread, one little bit of soap, and something like a coffee substitute in the morning.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Again, one month sharp.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were put clean and quarantined, and healthy into this time a real train, second class.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "First class-- [INAUDIBLE] not because we were so great.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But that's all they had available at the time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Only that these upholsteries were full of lice and fleas.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So when we finally came to the destination where we are supposed to be clean, not to spoil the new camp, well we were scratching and itching and infected.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I mean, nothing worked anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "From there we were sent to Ohrdruf.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Ohrdruf was where little outside camps, one, two, and three, which were in the woods, close to the forest, where in the morning we were sent out digging what should have become the great tunnel.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
